---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "../../components/shared/Container.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Flores Nexus Group LLC"
  description="Privacy Policy for Flores Nexus Group LLC. How we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
  lang="en"
>
  <main class="pt-24 pb-20">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

        <!-- Attorney notice -->
        <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 italic mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          This document is provided for informational purposes. Flores Nexus Group LLC recommends consulting a licensed Florida attorney before relying on these terms for legal decisions.
        </p>

        <!-- Page header -->
        <div class="mb-10">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-heading-1 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-heading-3 text-sm">Flores Nexus Group LLC — Last updated: June 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-0">

          <!-- Section 1 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">1</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Introduction</h2>
            <div class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
              <p>Flores Nexus Group LLC is committed to protecting the privacy of its clients, website users, and sales representatives. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, who we share it with, and what your rights are regarding that information.</p>
              <p>By using our website, submitting any form, completing the onboarding process, or purchasing any plan, you accept the practices described in this policy.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 2 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">2</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">What Information We Collect</h2>

            <div class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-heading-1 mb-2">2.1 Information you provide directly</p>
                <p class="mb-2">From the Start Your Website Form:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-heading-3 ml-2">
                  <li>Full name of primary contact</li>
                  <li>Business name</li>
                  <li>Phone number</li>
                  <li>Email address</li>
                  <li>City or service area</li>
                  <li>Business type and industry</li>
                  <li>Main services</li>
                  <li>Selected plan</li>
                  <li>Representative Code if applicable</li>
                  <li>Desired domain if applicable</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="mb-2">From the post-payment onboarding form:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-heading-3 ml-2">
                  <li>Full legal business name</li>
                  <li>Complete business contact information</li>
                  <li>Operating hours and service area</li>
                  <li>List of services offered</li>
                  <li>Logo, photos, images, and brand materials</li>
                  <li>Social media links and external platform links</li>
                  <li>Google Business Profile if applicable</li>
                  <li>Design preferences and colors</li>
                  <li>Testimonials and reviews if provided voluntarily</li>
                  <li>Any other information submitted voluntarily</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="mb-2">From direct communications:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-heading-3 ml-2">
                  <li>Emails, messages, and support requests</li>
                  <li>Change request submissions</li>
                  <li>Cancellation or transfer requests</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-heading-1 mb-2">2.2 Automatically collected information</p>
                <p class="mb-2">From the Flores Nexus website:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-heading-3 ml-2">
                  <li>Visitor IP address</li>
                  <li>Browser type and operating system</li>
                  <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
                  <li>Traffic source</li>
                  <li>Device type</li>
                  <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3 mb-2">From Stripe when processing payments:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-heading-3 ml-2">
                  <li>Payment confirmation and transaction status</li>
                  <li>Last 4 digits of card used</li>
                  <li>Billing country</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">Flores Nexus Group LLC does not store full card numbers — this data is processed and stored directly by Stripe.</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-heading-1 mb-2">2.3 Representative Code information</p>
                <p>When a client enters a Representative Code in the start form, we record the association between that code and the client order for attribution and commission purposes. This information is used internally and is not shared publicly.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 3 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">3</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <div class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 text-heading-2 ml-2">
                <li>To build, manage, and maintain the client website</li>
                <li>To process payments and manage subscriptions</li>
                <li>To communicate with the client about their order</li>
                <li>To send payment confirmations and billing notifications</li>
                <li>To complete the onboarding process</li>
                <li>To manage support requests and change requests</li>
                <li>To attribute sales to representatives via Representative Code</li>
                <li>To display the client business in the public directory if authorized</li>
                <li>To use client materials in portfolio or advertising if authorized</li>
                <li>To analyze traffic on the Flores Nexus website</li>
                <li>To comply with applicable legal obligations</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-4">We do not sell or rent client data to third parties. We do not share client data with advertisers.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 4 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">4</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Cookies</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">Our website may use essential cookies for site functionality, analytics cookies to understand visitor behavior, and preference cookies to remember settings such as selected language. Users can configure their browser to reject cookies. Rejecting essential cookies may affect site functionality.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 5 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">5</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Who We Share Information With</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">We share information only with service providers that help us operate the service, including Stripe for payment processing, hosting providers, domain registrars, and email communication tools. We may also disclose information if required by law or to protect our rights.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 6 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">6</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Public Directory</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">If the client authorized inclusion in the Flores Nexus public directory during onboarding, the following may be publicly visible: business name, category, service area, short description, logo or image, website link, and phone if authorized. This information remains visible while the subscription is active. Upon cancellation or written revocation, information will be removed within 15 business days.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 7 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">7</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Portfolio and Advertising Use</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">If the client authorized use of their materials during onboarding, Flores Nexus Group LLC may use the business name, logo, website image, and category in portfolio, social media, advertising campaigns, and sales materials. The client may revoke this permission at any time in writing. Revocation does not apply retroactively to materials already published.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 8 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">8</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Data Retention</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed ml-2">
              <li>Account and onboarding information: while subscription is active + 90 days after cancellation</li>
              <li>Payment and billing records: 7 years</li>
              <li>Support communications: 2 years</li>
              <li>Analytics data: 26 months</li>
              <li>Authorized portfolio materials: indefinite unless revoked</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 9 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">9</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Data Security</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">We implement reasonable security measures including HTTPS encryption, Stripe PCI-DSS compliant payment processing, and restricted access to client information. No security system is completely infallible. In the event of a security breach affecting personal information, we will notify affected parties within a reasonable timeframe as required by applicable law.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 10 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">10</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal information. You may revoke directory, portfolio, or advertising permissions at any time. You may request a copy of your original content within 30 days of service cancellation. To exercise these rights, contact us at [Floresnexusgroup@gmail.com].</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 11 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">11</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Minors</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">Our services are directed to business owners and are not designed for individuals under 18 years of age.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 12 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">12</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">We may update this policy at any time. Material changes will be notified by email with at least 7 days notice when practical. Continued use of the service after the effective date constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 13 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">13</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Governing Law</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed">This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of the State of Florida, United States.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 14 -->
          <div class="py-6 border-t border-box-border">
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">14</p>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Contact</h2>
            <div class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed space-y-1">
              <p class="font-medium text-heading-1">Flores Nexus Group LLC</p>
              <p>Email: [Floresnexusgroup@gmail.com]</p>
              <p>Website: [OFFICIAL URL]</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </main>
</Layout>
